From 0ac69abdc5ae24353157ec1c8fb41c051bf0da85 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rex Lu <rex.lu@mediatek.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 13:47:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: mtk_wed: reduce busy poll timeout

Reduce the WED busy poll interval from 15 ms to 1 ms. MediaTek notes
that the longer interval can make L1 SER spend several seconds under
heavy bidirectional traffic, delaying WED idle state recovery and causing
station disconnects.

Signed-off-by: Rex Lu <rex.lu@mediatek.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_wed.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_wed.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_wed.c
@@ -276,7 +276,7 @@ mtk_wed_check_busy(struct mtk_wed_device
 static int
 mtk_wed_poll_busy(struct mtk_wed_device *dev, u32 reg, u32 mask)
 {
-	int sleep = 15000;
+	int sleep = 1000;
 	int timeout = 100 * sleep;
 	u32 val;
 
